The article highlights the Obama administration's accomplishments in Sub-Saharan Africa. These include engaging with young African leaders through the President's Young African Leaders Initiative, strengthening democratic institutions, promoting peace and security, investing in sustainable development, and promoting trade and investment. The administration has supported democratic processes in countries like Cote d'Ivoire and Kenya, promoted peace in Sudan and efforts to combat the Lord's Resistance Army (LRA), and invested in initiatives like Feed the Future to address hunger and poverty. The United States has also supported health programs, climate change initiatives, and trade partnerships with African countries.